snakeOS mkosi (optional, Linux hosts)

1. Build a rootfs (recommended: systemd standard edition for mainstream compatibility):

   sudo ./scripts/build-rootfs-debian-standard.sh

2. Adjust `mkosi/mkosi.conf` if your rootfs directory differs.
3. From the repository root:

   mkosi --directory mkosi

mkosi evolves quickly; treat this as a starting point. The standard rootfs
already includes a Debian kernel metapackage and GRUB EFI binaries; the live
installer script finishes bootloader installation onto real disks.
